cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with medical image classification using deep neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a framework for dealing with noisy-labeled data, which is a common problem in machine learning, and thus falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The proposed method involves uncertainty sampling and sample re-weighting, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also validates the proposed method on skin lesion classification, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) related to medical imaging.
